{
  "texts": [
    "Learning criteria permit to establish a metric for quantifying the gains of all the possible learner decisions, and prescribe an optimal decision based in information acquired from the surrogate model.",
    "The vast majority of the literature concerning pool-based active learning identifies three essential learning criteria: informativeness, representativeness and diversity [46,93,126,141,144,153]:1.",
    "Informativeness measures the amount of information encoded by a certain sample.",
    "This means that the sampling policy is driven by the maximum likely contribution of queries that would significantly benefit the objective of the learning procedure. 2.",
    "Representativeness quantifies the similarity of a sample or a group of samples with respect to a target sample representative of the target distribution."
  ]
}